
Roguelike Console Game
A simple roguelike game built in C++17 using the ncurses library.
Navigate the player @ through a procedurally generated dungeon map, avoiding enemies E that chase you.
Use arrow keys to move the player @

Features include:
    Procedurally generated map with walls and open spaces
    Player movement constrained by map boundaries and walls
    Basic enemy AI that moves toward the player slowly
    Game over condition when an enemy catches the player
    Console rendering with ncurses for smooth text-based graphics
    This project demonstrates core game engine concepts, basic AI, and design patterns in a console environment.